canonical:
  title: 走筆寄江陵李使君
  author: 李存吾
  language: lzh
  text: 海闊天高一郡平州城人道是逢瀛霓旌羽盖寒松月想像風流太守行
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 走筆寄江陵李使君
  author: 李存吾
  language: lzh
  text: 海闊天高一郡平。州城人道是逢瀛。霓旌羽盖寒松月。想像風流太守行。
korean:
  title: 붓을 들어 빨리 써서 강릉 이사에게 부침
  author: 이존오
  language: kor
  text: |-
    바다는 넓고 하늘은 높은데 한 고을이 펀펀하니
    사람들은 이 고을 성을 봉영이라 이른다
    신선의 무지개 깃발과 깃일산 놀던 한송정의 달
    풍류 태수의 노는 것이 상상되네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0240_010_0660&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: A Hasty Brush to the Governor of Gangreung
  author: Lee Joon-o
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The sea spreads wide, the sky stretches high—one prefecture lies serene and level.
    The townspeople call this city the Blessed Land of Immortals.
    Rainbow banners and feathered canopies dance beneath the moon at Cold Pine Pavilion.
    I imagine the graceful wanderings of our cultivated governor.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: Gangreung (江陵) is located in present-day Gangwon Province, Korea
  - key: ''
    value: The 'Blessed Land of Immortals' (逢瀛) alludes to mythical utopias in classical Chinese literature, suggesting the governor has brought prosperity and peace to the region
  - key: ''
    value: Cold Pine Pavilion (한松) evokes a place of refined aesthetic appreciation
  - key: ''
    value: The 'cultivated governor' (風流太守) refers to the recipient, Li, suggesting he embodies both administrative excellence and artistic refinement
